<s docid="FT934-6885" num="4"> FT 23 NOV 93 / Tebbit attacks European move</s>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<s docid="FT934-6885" num="5"> Lord Tebbit last night accused Britain's political establishment - the government and the opposition parties - of disorientating and destabilising the nation.</s>

<s docid="FT934-6885" num="6"> The former Tory minister and party chairman claimed that parliament was 'living on borrowed time', subservient to Brussels and impotent.</s>

<s docid="FT934-6885" num="7"> He said: 'What are we to make of a governing party which, with the full support of the two opposition parties, had dedicated itself to the dissolving of the superglue of nationality'?</s>

<s docid="FT934-6885" num="8"> Lord Tebbit also warned that Britain was 'drifting towards becoming a largely pagan society' in which some churches were blessing homosexual liaisons and where polygamy was recognised when once bigamists were criminals.</s>
</TEXT>
